The paper discusses the decline and obsolescence of Microsoft Academic Search, which is a search engine for academic publications. The paper analyzes the coverage of disciplines and journals, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybernetics (cs.CY), databases (cs.DB), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
